{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6e56da19-11a2-46c6-81af-4333835e10b1","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** by `dotnet test` — that's why your settings are ignored. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's the mapping from your current config:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout = 30000` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| Code Coverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectors>` with `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | No longer needed (modern test host handles this) |\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` and wire it up:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NsgHBEqrF1dd9AdcYZDbAB","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9008453c12594c659692bb642ec59d2e/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.SingleFileCollector, Microsoft.CodeCoverage, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-9008453c12594c659692bb642ec59d2e/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Hne1nuV9CFzKwgS4RqN6u8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9008453c12594c659692bb642ec59d2e/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9008453c12594c659692bb642ec59d2e/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"5aa7e46c-9844-4363-9ba7-e96dd75bce2d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file that's being ignored after upgrading to MSTest 3.x. The `.testsettings` format is legacy and not supported by modern `dotnet test`. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nLet me create the equivalent `.runsettings` file and update the project.\n\nThe `.testsettings` has:\n1. **Test deployment** (`AssemblyResolution` with `useLoadContext`) — not needed in modern MSTest; deployment is handled differently.\n2. **TestTimeout** of 30000ms (30 seconds) — maps to `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` in `.runsettings`, or better yet, use `[Timeout]` attribute or MSTest's `TestTimeout` setting.\n\n\n3. **Code Coverage data collector** — I'll need to configure this in the `<DataCollectors>` section of the `.runsettings` file.\n\nNow I'll create the `.runsettings` file with these settings and update the project file to reference it.","outputTokens":913,"requestId":"7C15:1EA0BA:17037D0:1A2DE0D:69F958E9"},"id":"b9c2ee6c-2273-4cf3-b349-d1e43fa3d91c","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:42:43.626Z","parentId":"6dab1015-7a5b-439b-b1d7-acd52ee0a112"}
